    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Mane applications tend to use separate data folders for the roaming user profile and caching databases.\r\n\r\nThe roaming profile includes configuration and other data that was \"entered by the user\". It is the minimal amount of files that you need to synchronize between two computers to recreate the same user experience. It's usually small.\r\n\r\nThe caching database is something that can recreated from the information in the roaming profile. It can include significantly more data such as chat histories, downloaded media files, web3 browsing caches, etc. \r\n\r\nThe usual suggested directories for the two data folders:\r\n\r\nWindows:\r\n\r\nRoaming profile: %HOME%\\AppData\\Roaming\\Status\\\r\nCache directory: %HOME%\\AppData\\Local\\Status\\\r\n\r\nLinux: \r\n\r\nRoaming profile: `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/status` (by default `${HOME}/.config/status/`)\r\nCache directory: `$XDG_CACHE_HOME/status`  (by default `${HOME}/.cache/status/`)\r\n\r\nmacOS:\r\n\r\nRoaming profile: `${HOME}/Library/Preferences/Status`\r\nCache directory: `${HOME}/Library/Application Support/Status`",
