    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Without being fully certain, I expect that the `DATADIR` in Status Go stores the downloaded blockchain data, which is not personal and can be downloaded from public sources on any machine, so it can be safely treated as a cache directory.\r\n\r\nThe Keystores are personal data, but it's a matter of UX design to decide whether the passwords for unlocking them should be device-specific. If the passwords are device-specific, the keystores should also go in the \"local data\" dir. Otherwise they can be considered part of the roaming profile.",
